        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 8 at 3:27AM CDT by NWS Amarillo TX</headline>
        <description>At 327 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Groom, or 15 miles east of Claude, moving southeast at 35 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Howardwick, Lake Mcclellan, Mclean, Claude, Alanreed, Groom,
Clarendon, Greenbelt Lake, and Goodnight.

This includes Interstate 40 between mile markers 105 and 143.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
